[30;1m376 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m377 | [0m[35m    The ostinato algorithm proposed in the paper finds the best radius[0m
[30;1m378 | [0m[35m    in `Ts`. Intuitively, the radius is the minimum distance of a[0m
[30;1m379 | [0m[35m    subsequence to encompass at least one nearest neighbor subsequence[0m
[30;1m380 | [0m[35m    from all other time series. The best radius in `Ts` is the minimum[0m
[30;1m381 | [0m[35m    radius amongst all radii. Some data sets might contain multiple[0m
[30;1m382 | [0m[35m    subsequences which have the same optimal radius.[0m

[30;1m64 | [0m[35m        using ``functools.partial``. Any subsequence with at least one[0m
[30;1m65 | [0m[35m        ``np.nan``/``np.inf`` will automatically have its corresponding value set to[0m
[30;1m66 | [0m[35m        ``False`` in this boolean array.[0m
[30;1m67 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m468 | [0m[35m    The ostinato algorithm proposed in the paper finds the best radius[0m
[30;1m469 | [0m[35m    in ``Ts``. Intuitively, the radius is the minimum distance of a[0m
[30;1m470 | [0m[35m    subsequence to encompass at least one nearest neighbor subsequence[0m
[30;1m471 | [0m[35m    from all other time series. The best radius in ``Ts`` is the minimum[0m
[30;1m472 | [0m[35m    radius amongst all radii. Some data sets might contain multiple[0m
[30;1m473 | [0m[35m    subsequences which have the same optimal radius.[0m

[30;1m342 | [0m[35m    The ostinato algorithm proposed in the paper finds the best radius[0m
[30;1m343 | [0m[35m    in ``Ts``. Intuitively, the radius is the minimum distance of a[0m

[30;1m211 | [0m[35m    The ostinato algorithm proposed in the paper finds the best radius[0m
[30;1m212 | [0m[35m    in `Ts`. Intuitively, the radius is the minimum distance of a[0m
[30;1m213 | [0m[35m    subsequence to encompass at least one nearest neighbor subsequence[0m
[30;1m214 | [0m[35m    from all other time series. The best radius in `Ts` is the minimum[0m
[30;1m215 | [0m[35m    radius amongst all radii. Some data sets might contain multiple[0m
[30;1m216 | [0m[35m    subsequences which have the same optimal radius.[0m
[30;1m217 | [0m[35m    The greedy Ostinato algorithm only finds one of them, which might[0m

[30;1m56 | [0m[35m    The ostinato algorithm proposed in the paper finds the best radius[0m
[30;1m57 | [0m[35m    in `Ts`. Intuitively, the radius is the minimum distance of a[0m
[30;1m58 | [0m[35m    subsequence to encompass at least one nearest neighbor subsequence[0m
[30;1m59 | [0m[35m    from all other time series. The best radius in `Ts` is the minimum[0m

[30;1m61 | [0m[35m    subsequences which have the same optimal radius.[0m

[30;1m3025 | [0m[35m    the position of the leaf nodes from the indices alone (i.e., a leaf node could be[0m
[30;1m3026 | [0m[35m    attached to any parent node from a previous layer). For example, if `n = 9` then[0m
[30;1m3027 | [0m[35m    the corresponding (zero-based index) balanced binary tree is:[0m

[30;1m3398 | [0m[35mdef _shift_insert_at_index(a, idx, v, shift="right"):[0m
[30;1m3399 | [0m[35m    """[0m
[30;1m3400 | [0m[35m    If `shift=right` (default), all elements in `a[idx:]` are shifted to the right by[0m
[30;1m3401 | [0m[35m    one element, `v` in inserted at index `idx` and the last element is discarded.[0m
[30;1m3402 | [0m[35m    If `shift=left`, all elements in `a[:idx]` are shifted to the left by one element,[0m

[30;1m3404 | [0m[35m    `a` is updated in place and its length remains unchanged.[0m

[30;1m3333 | [0m[35m    process when the inputs are 2D arrays)[0m
[30;1m3334 | [0m[35m    When the inputs are 2D arrays, we always prioritize the values of `ρA` over[0m
[30;1m3335 | [0m[35m    the values of `ρB` in case of ties. (i.e., values from `ρB` are always inserted[0m
[30;1m3336 | [0m[35m    to the left of values from `ρA`). Also, update `IA` accordingly. In case of[0m
[30;1m3337 | [0m[35m    overlapping values between two arrays IA[i] and IB[i], the ones in IB[i] (and[0m

   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m77 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m78 | [0m[35m    The ostinato algorithm proposed in the paper finds the best radius[0m
[30;1m79 | [0m[35m    in ``Ts``. Intuitively, the radius is the minimum distance of a[0m
[30;1m80 | [0m[35m    subsequence to encompass at least one nearest neighbor subsequence[0m
[30;1m81 | [0m[35m    from all other time series. The best radius in ``Ts`` is the minimum[0m
[30;1m82 | [0m[35m    radius amongst all radii. Some data sets might contain multiple[0m
[30;1m83 | [0m[35m    subsequences which have the same optimal radius.[0m
